wikipedia_page.main: James Robert Bracey (born 3 May 1997) is an English cricketer who plays for Gloucestershire County Cricket Club.  He is a left-handed batsman, who also plays as a wicket-keeper. He made his first-class debut for Gloucestershire against Sussex in September 2016. He made his international debut for the England cricket team in June 2021. His brother, Sam, has also played first-class cricket.
